This course examines the strategic, technological, competitive, economic, organizational, and political challenges impacting the pharmaceutical and biotechnology industry. Learning outcomes to be gained by the students include:
•R&D - process of discovering, developing, and approving new drugs & biologics;
•Regulatory environment and IP/patents; orphan drugs; generics and “biosimilars”;
•Global launch and competitive market dynamics of new biopharmaceuticals – U.S. and international markets;
•Oncology category: clinical/regulatory, commercial issues/pricing & reimbursement, personalized medicine/ use of biomarkers, etc.
•Drug pricing and third-party reimbursement, including design of prescription drug plans, role/practices of PBMs, and drug provisions of the Inflation Reduction Act;
•Unique challenges of creating, managing, and investing in early/commercial-stage biopharma companies;
